{{Infobox football biography |name = Harry Keggans |image = |image_size = |caption = |fullname = Henry Keggans |birth_date = 4 December 1887<ref>Certificate available at [https://www.scotlandspeople.gov.uk https://www.scotlandspeople.gov.uk] {{small|(payment required)}}</ref> |birth_place = [[Cambuslang]], Scotland |death_date= {{dda|1949|8|20|1887|12|4|df=y}}<ref>England & Scotland, Select Cemetery Registers, 1800-2016</ref> |death_place=[[Sanquhar]], Scotland |height = |position = [[Inside forward|Inside right]] |youthyears1 = |youthclubs1 = |years1 = |clubs1 = Sanquhar |caps1 = |goals1 = |years2 = 1911–1912 |clubs2 = [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]] |caps2 = 1 |goals2 = 0 |years3 = |clubs3 = [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]] |caps3 = |goals3 = |totalcaps = |totalgoals = }} '''Harry Keggans''' (4 December 1887 – 20 August 1949) was a Scottish professional [[association football|footballer]] who played as an [[Inside forward|inside right]].
Keggans was born in [[Cambuslang]], [[Lanarkshire]] to Henry Keggans and Elizabeth McSephney Keggans, and moved to [[New Cumnock]], [[Ayrshire]] shortly afterward.<ref>1891 Scotland Census</ref> Keggans signed for [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]] in October 1911 from Sanquhar, leaving the club in August 1912 to play for [[Cardiff City F.C.|Cardiff City]].<ref>Frost, p. 400</ref> During his time with Bradford City he made one appearance in the Football League.<ref>Frost, p. 384</ref>
He died of coronary thrombosis in 1949.<ref>{{cite web|title=1949 Keggans, Henry (Statutory Deaths 848/00 00 18)|url=https://www.ancestry.com/mediaui-viewer/tree/5901559/person/1019469884/media/7c9852eb-c7a6-4c8e-af21-77cad7ff0911|accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref>
