{{Infobox Politician | name = John Cascaden | image = | imagesize = | office1 = [[Member of Provincial Parliament (Ontario)|Ontario MPP]] | term_start1 = 1879 | term_end1 = 1886 | predecessor1 = [[David McLaws]] | successor1 = [[Andrew B. Ingram]] | constituency1 = [[Elgin West (provincial electoral district)|Elgin West]] | party = [[Ontario Liberal Party|Liberal]] | birth_date = {{birth date|1840|12|3}} | birth_place = [[Ballyshannon]], [[County Donegal]], [[Ireland]] | death_date = {{death date and age|1904|8|31|1840|12|3}} | death_place = [[Dutton, Ontario]] | occupation = | relations = | spouse = Hannah Katherine Decou (m. 1872) | children = 5 }} '''John Cascaden''' (December 3, 1840 &ndash; August 31, 1904) was an [[Ontario]] physician and political figure. He represented [[Elgin West (provincial electoral district)|Elgin West]] in the [[Legislative Assembly of Ontario]] from 1879 to 1886 as a [[Liberal Party of Ontario|Liberal]] members.
He was born in [[Ballyshannon]], [[County Donegal]], [[Ireland]] in 1840 and came to [[Bruce County, Ontario|Bruce County]], [[Canada West]] with his family in 1852. He studied at the [[University of Toronto]], receiving an [[Doctor of Medicine|M.D.]] in 1863, and at the [[Royal College of Physicians]] in [[London]], [[England]]. After his first wife died at a young age, Cascaden married Hannah Katherine Decou in 1872. John and Hannah had five children: David Arthur (b: 1874), Annie May (b:1875), John Harold (b:1879), Douglas Jerald (b:1881), and Gordon L. (b:1884). He served as [[coroner]] for [[Elgin County, Ontario|Elgin County]]. John died in August 1904 and is buried in the cemetery of St. Stephen's Anglican Church in [[Dutton/Dunwich, Ontario|Dunwich]], [[Elgin County, Ontario|Elgin County]], [[Ontario]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://familysearch.org/pal:/MM9.1.1/J64S-Z2R |title=Person Details for John Cascaden |publisher=Familysearch.org |date= |accessdate=2016-08-02}}</ref>
