{{BLP sources|date=August 2010}}'''Mariann Aalda''' (born May 7, 1948) is an American television, stage, film actress, performance artist, and stand-up comic.
==Career== She is best known for her work in television as DiDi Bannister-Stoner on ABC's ''[[The Edge of Night]]'' from 1981 until the show's cancellation in 1984. Later, she appeared on the CBS show ''[[Guiding Light]]''. She also had regular roles on the [[CBS]] sitcom ''[[The Royal Family (TV series)|The Royal Family]]'', as the daughter of [[Redd Foxx]] and [[Della Reese]], and the [[HBO]] series ''[[1st & Ten (HBO TV series)|1st & Ten]]'', as the wife of [[O.J. Simpson]]'s character.
Aalda also achieved notoriety recurring on the CBS sitcom, ''Designing Women'', as Anthony's yuppie-from-hell girlfriend, Lita Ford, and on the [[NBC]] soap opera ''[[Sunset Beach (TV series)|Sunset Beach]]'' as the tragically disfigured Lena Hart. Additionally, she co-hosted the lifestyle show ''Designs for Living'' on the USA Network and was a reporter for the magazine show ''NOW!'' on WNBC in New York. Her numerous guest-star roles are mostly sitcom.
Aalda has also appeared in movies, co-starring in the urban cult film ''[[Class Act]]'' as rapper Kid's clueless mom, and as Coach Harrison in Nobody's Perfect. She was also a featured player in ''Beaches'' and ''Pretty Woman'', directed by Garry Marshall
